# Deployment — DolphinSystems.net

## Quick Deploy

After making any code changes, deploy to production with:

```bash
npm run deploy
```

This single command builds, syncs to the Raspberry Pi, and restarts the server. The site goes live at https://dolphinsystems.net.

## Architecture

- **Hosting**: Raspberry Pi at `pi@ritik.local` (local network)
- **Public access**: Cloudflare Tunnel exposes the Pi to the internet
- **Domain**: dolphinsystems.net (DNS managed by Cloudflare)
- **SSL**: Handled automatically by Cloudflare
- **Stack on Pi**:
  - `cloudflared` — tunnel service (systemd, auto-starts on boot)
  - `nginx` — reverse proxy on port 80
  - `PM2` + `Next.js standalone` — app server on port 3000
  - Files live at `/var/www/dolphinsystems/`

## Important Notes

- `next.config.ts` must keep `output: "standalone"` — this is required for the deployment to work.
- Environment variables (Supabase keys) are in `.env.local` and get synced to the Pi on every deploy.
- After deploying, always confirm the site is live: `curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" https://dolphinsystems.net` should return `200`.
- If the Pi is unreachable, make sure it's powered on and connected to the same network.

## Troubleshooting on the Pi (via SSH)

```bash
ssh pi@ritik.local
pm2 status                    # check if Next.js is running
pm2 logs dolphinsystems       # view app logs
sudo systemctl status cloudflared   # check tunnel
sudo systemctl status nginx         # check nginx
```
